{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.28",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 28,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 28",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 28 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:1",
      "text": "“ Surely there is a mine for silver, and a place for gold which they refine.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:2",
      "text": "Iron is taken out of the earth, and copper is smelted out of the ore.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:3",
      "text": "Man sets an end to darkness, and searches out, to the furthest bound, the stones of obscurity and of thick darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:4",
      "text": "He breaks open a shaft away from where people live. They are forgotten by the foot. They hang far from men, they swing back and forth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:5",
      "text": "As for the earth, out of it comes bread. Underneath it is turned up as it were by fire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:6",
      "text": "Sapphires come from its rocks. It has dust of gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:7",
      "text": "That path no bird of prey knows, neither has the falcon’s eye seen it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:8",
      "text": "The proud animals have not trodden it, nor has the fierce lion passed by there.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:9",
      "text": "He puts his hand on the flinty rock, and he overturns the mountains by the roots.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:10",
      "text": "He cuts out channels among the rocks. His eye sees every precious thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:11",
      "text": "He binds the streams that they don’t trickle. The thing that is hidden he brings out to light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:12",
      "text": "“But where will wisdom be found? Where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:13",
      "text": "Man doesn’t know its price, and it isn’t found in the land of the living.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:14",
      "text": "The deep says, ‘ It isn’t in me.’ The sea says, ‘ It isn’t with me.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:15",
      "text": "It can ’t be gotten for gold, neither will silver be weighed for its price.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:16",
      "text": "It can ’t be valued with the gold of Ophir, with the precious onyx, or the sapphire.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:17",
      "text": "Gold and glass can ’t equal it, neither will it be exchanged for jewels of fine gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:18",
      "text": "No mention will be made of coral or of crystal. Yes, the price of wisdom is above rubies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:19",
      "text": "The topaz of Ethiopia will not equal it. It won’t be valued with pure gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:20",
      "text": "Where then does wisdom come from? Where is the place of understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:21",
      "text": "Seeing it is hidden from the eyes of all living, and kept close from the birds of the sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:22",
      "text": "Destruction and Death say, ‘ We have heard a rumor of it with our ears.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:23",
      "text": "“God understands its way, and he knows its place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:24",
      "text": "For he looks to the ends of the earth, and sees under the whole sky.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:25",
      "text": "He establishes the force of the wind. Yes, he measures out the waters by measure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:26",
      "text": "When he made a decree for the rain, and a way for the lightning of the thunder,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:27",
      "text": "then he saw it, and declared it. He established it, yes, and searched it out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.28.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 28,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 28:28",
      "text": "To man he said, ‘ Behold, the fear of the Lord, that is wisdom. To depart from evil is understanding.’”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
